audio_descriptions.notes:
We see a mountain road. Next to the road is a crossing sign and a sign that reads, "Cloudburst Summit, Elevation 7018 feet".
A white van drives down the road.
Andan enters a diner.
Andan sits in a diner booth with Crothers.
We Cheryl sitting on a park bench. Malvin approaches and sits on the bench.
Malvin brushes a lock of hair behind Cheryl's ear, and they look at each other.
A cube on a pedestal in a dimly lit red room.
Cheryl stands by Dad's messy computer desk, talking to Daughter. Daughter begins to twitch sporadically and leaves.
Dadbot stands in a closet with his eyes closed. Cheryl bursts in and kisses on the cheek. He opens his eyes and looks at her, smiling.
We see the cube with two red lights blinking inside of it.
Dad sits at a desk with a computer and a huge stack of papers. Marty sits next to him at another desk. Boss stands between them and hands Dad the e-phone.
We see the cube with three lights blinking inside of it.
Dad stands with Diane among scattered papers. Diane gestures throwing up and then rocking a baby. Dad collapses to the floor. Diane runs off.
We see the cube with dozens of small red lights inside of it.
Cheryl and Crothers in an empty room. They stare each other down. Cheryl slaps herself and disappears.
Cheryl wakes up in bed next to someone.
Cheryl and Malvin argue in a room with a table. Cheryl slaps Malvin. Cheryl grabs Malvin's hand as he begins to walk away. Malvin pulls his hand away and leaves.
A client drinks from a mug and looks at Dad, who is unconscious on the floor.
A client drinks from a mug while looking at the closet Cheryl and Dadbot are in. Dadbot leaves. Daughter twitches sporadically in the background.
An arm in a red flannel shirt holds a Nerf gun. A light flashes on the Nerf gun.
Someone drags a Client away.
Someone drags Griffin away.
The arm in flannel shoots Dadbot with the Nerf gun, and Dadbot collapses.
Griffin and a Client are upside down in metal garbage cans, their legs sticking straight up.
Text and a loading bar appears onscreen. 
Dad stands in an empty room, looking down. He is holding a briefcase and a coffee mug.
A red orb appears and disappears.
Dad looks up.
A white van drives through the desert.
Nathan lies unconscious in the desert. The van pulls up to him and stops.
A spacesuit in the back of a van. There is faint pink mist floating around the spacesuit. Nathan lies in the desert and recedes from view.
A striped planet looms unusually large in the sky.
Nathan and the space suit in the back of the van. The pink mist moves from the spacesuit to Nathan.
A shot of Dad's video "Real Zombie Virus - Crazy But True". It shows an illustration of an ant with a smiling mushroom coming out of its head. It then shows someone pressing on a mushroom and spores coming out of it.
We see Nathan lying unconscious in the desert with a man standing next to him. We can't see the man's face, but he is wearing a red flannel shirt and jeans.
Nathan unconscious in the back of the van. Faint pink mist floats around his mouth.
Shot of Daughter on a sound stage. The shot pans up, revealing a suburban town with a True Value and an IHOP in its center.
The shot pans up to another empty sound stage, then to a variety of wires and electronic components.
Text reads "Act 3 continues".
Fade to black.

Text reads "2017".
Cheryl and Malvin sit on the park bench. Malvin is rubbing his temples.
Malvin begins to get up, but Cheryl grabs him and kisses him.
They stare at each other. Malvin puts his earpiece back in.
Cut to black.
Text reads "2020".
Fade in on a white van parked next to some benches outside a building. Nathan lies unconscious on one of the benches.
The van drives away.
Black and white footage of the inside of an apartment.
Nathan stumbles into the apartment.
Nathan sways and steadies himself against a wall. He takes a few steps forward, then kneels down on the floor. He collapses, unconscious.
Fade to a shot of the apartment at a later time. Nathan is gone.
Nathan suddenly appears, standing completely still. He is naked, and he has no genitals.
In a blur, Nathan suddenly moves to another part of the apartment and stands perfectly still.
Nathan continues to intermittently move in a blur to different parts of the apartment and stand completely still.
Nathan looks at the camera and leaps toward it. Cut to black.
Pan down to a street light at night.
Pan down to show Nathan standing above a young woman who is lying in the street.  A stream of pink mist moves from Nathan's mouth to the woman. There is a portable cassette player next to her.
Nathan collapses onto the street.
A black van drives up to them and stops.
A man comes out of the van, wearing a black hoodie that obscures his face. There is an orange swirl on the back of his hoodie.
The man opens the trunk of his van.
He drags the woman toward the van.
He puts her into the trunk.
He closes the trunk.
He brushes his hands off and gets back into the van.
He begins to drive away.
The van stops, then reverses back toward Nathan.
The van stops, and the man runs out.
He runs over to the cassette player and picks it up.
He runs back to the van with the cassette player and drives away.
End card reads, "New Dad merch in description". It shows a hoodie with an image of Dad squeezing a can of FOOD into his mouth like Popeye, then it shows a hoodie with an image of Andan in his space suit.
End card reads, "Subscribe to Dad. Twitter and Instagram at Dad Feels." There are video links to "The Facility" and "The Last of Him".
